Description: Plate II, illustration to an unidentified work; eight images of antiquarian objects, marked "fig. 1 to fig. 8."; in top two rows four coins and their reverses; below, a scene with two men making a rope next to a haystack, using a special tool; below on left, Egyptian goddess Hathor preparing to suckle a child on her knee; on right, a medal lettered "Vota P vblica", and in foreground in centre a dog holding a lyre; border of single line on top and left, and double line on bottom and right. Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: One of two plates of similar formats, probably intended for the same publication - also see 1850,0223.624
Bibliographic references: Alexander 2008 / George Vertue as an Engraver (1046)
